                   "message":  "MENU-SHORTCUT-DOC-RECONCILE: record File/Edit accelerators (#304) + menu extraction (#305), docs-only\n\nForward-only planning-substrate hygiene closing the menu-deepening thread.\nRecords that #304 (284998e, MENU-SHORTCUT-DISPLAY) shipped File/Edit accelerator\nDISPLAY (Open Ctrl+O / Save Ctrl+S / Save-As Ctrl+Shift+S / Undo Ctrl+Z / Redo\nCtrl+Y via egui shortcut_text, sourced from the existing editor-ui Shortcut\nsubstrate on MenuEntry.shortcut) and #305 (892a0ad, EGUIHOST-MENU-EXTRACTION)\nextracted the menu construction into a menu.rs submodule (behaviour-identical) +\nretired the split-cap exemption (lib.rs 1062 -\u003e 836, 0 markers crate-wide).\n\nPrepends a 2026-06-04 snapshot to Status.md + HANDOFF.md, inserts a new\n\"2026-06-04 - File/Edit menu accelerators shown; menu construction extracted to a\nsubmodule (#304 + #305)\" subsection into plans/BASELINE.md above the #302\nsubsection, and appends a matching change.md entry. All prior dated entries\n(PLAYMENU-DYNAMIC / A4 / A3 / A2 / A1 + older) byte-identical (pure\nprepend/insert/append, +29/-0).\n\nPrecise (no over-claim): narrows the prior \"accelerator-table\nexecution/display/conflict population\" deferred line -- the DISPLAY half shipped,\nfor File/Edit only. Still deferred: accelerator EXECUTION + conflict population;\nPlay/View accelerator display; W08 dynamic predicates + per-frame re-resolve;\ndynamic toggle labels; plugin entries; generalized registry/accelerator command\nexecution (clicks still use the FIFO). Display-only; clicks still dispatch via the\nFIFO; the shown values mirror the live EditorKeyCommand + Ctrl+O routing (host\ncan\u0027t import editor-shell), pinned by host tests.\n\nDocs-only: no Rust / Cargo / rustdoc / lint-doc change (#304 + #305 made their\nrustdoc current themselves). Gate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (Markdown-only).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
